# What is this? Read the .gitlabels README:
#   <https://github.com/elliottcable/.gitlabels>

# Core (at least one of these should apply to every commit)
- (new) new functionality or content
- (re refactor) subtle improvement, no intentional behavioural change visible to consumers, unless paired with (API)/(BRK)
- (fix:<issue_id> fixes closes) fixes a bug or problem, optional issue-ID

# Importance markers
- (- minor) unimportant / safe to skim past. typos, auto-reformats, mechanical, etc
  - (typo) typofix
- (!!) major / widespread / "landing a huge refactor"
- (API) public API surface change, contract
  - (BRK) breaking change (almost always paired with (!!))

# Authorship
- (AI) LLM-authored commit; mandatory on every AI-created commit

# Behavioural impact
- (tests) does *not* modify any implementation code, in any way (instead, indicates modifying code in the test suite)
- (noop) as (tests), except indicates that a commit does not modify any code belonging to the test suite either
  - (style) as (noop), because it only changes alignment/spacing/visual orientation of code or documentation
  - (doc) as (noop), because only change comments, documentation, etc (exclusive of actual *executed* code)
  - (meta) as (noop), performing only meta-project changes, not affecting runtime/production behavoiour (config, packaging, CI, etc)
    - (CI) changes to automated build, pipelines, GH actions, release, etc

# General
- (dep) dependency management
  - (up) bumping a dependency / SDK / lib version (often paired with `dep`)
- (rm) removal of something not just a code-deletion (often paired: `(rm dep)`)
- (sec) security
- (UI) user-interface / visual fidelity / layout
  - (extr) live-extraction of Klei prefab values into OniUiTokens
- (input) keyboard / mouse / hotkey handling
- (Klei) Klei-internals interop (reflection, harmony, decomp-cribbing)

# Functionality (don't dupe filenames / modules; only for cross-cutting areas)
- (MRU) most-recently-used feature surface
- (search) ranking / fuzzy / SearchUtil-related
